item.title: [HUB-276] Lit Drop count issue
item.description:
Hey,

I have been doing lit drops in West Jefferson A (Madison County) and I have found an issue with the printouts I have. On the sheets from Hubble, there is a number of "doors" at the top, a map with pins of each house to drop at, and then each address with check boxes for results of the canvass and whether they have yard signs or not. I have realized that none of these numbers are the same on the sheets I have. For example, for W. Jeff 1.7 the number of doors is 37, the number of pins on the map is 26, and the number of addresses is 24. I have 8 different walk sheets and they all have this issue. If you need me to scan in a sheet to show you what I am talking about I can do that as well. I am continuing the lit drops but if you find out what went wrong please let me know!

Thanks,

–
Tori King
Madison County Manager
(614) 937-6398

item.title: [HUB-214] Add help text for Interaction Results
item.description:
Busy: The line is busy
Call Back: they ask to be called at a different time
Contacted: Spoke to you about the campaign and seemed receptive but did not have email
Contribution: The caller makes a contribution
Deceased: The original number holder that we have on file is deceased.
Disconnected: Phone number is disconnected
Don Not Call: They ask to have their name taken off the list
Do Not Text: N/A
Email Updated: Used for when voter gives you their email
Inaccessible: Phone is no longer in service
Left Message With Someone:
Left Message: Left a message on their voicemail
Moved: They do not live in. OH-15 anymore
Non-Citizen: Not a citizen of OH-15
Not Home: Somebody else picks up the phone and says the intended contact is not home
Other: Any weird situation that does not apply to the other results- describe in notes.
Other Language: Voter is speaking in a language other than Spanish or English
Refused: Hung up during call or said they were not interested
Spanish: Voter is speaking in Spanish
Texted: N/A
Voicemail Full: Did not pick up and could not leave message
Wrong Number: Number does not match contact information.
item.summary: Add help text for Interaction Results

item.title: [HUB-200] Finance Filling Periods
item.description:
Hubble needs to track the time periods that a campaign is required to report their financial activity. They’ll be different for each campaign but some might have common occurrences.

They should also be able to track the reporting authority for the period.

A clone feature would be handy!

The periods will always start on the day following the end of the previous period. If the committee started in the middle of a period, the start date is considered the date the committee opened or their first recorded activity. This means we’ll need to track the open date of the committee.

item.title: [HUB-198] Volunteer Hub
item.description:
Originally, this issue was for a generic page to allow volunteers to sign up with my campaign. However, after further discussions with Joel Newby we’re going to create a Volunteer Hub within Hubble.

Rather than having a general page where they select the duties they want, volunteers will register for a Hubble user account and follow the same process as those signing up for phone banking. Once a user signs in, they’ll be greeted with the Volunteer Hub, the redesigned dashboard for volunteers. This Hub will serve as a central point for a volunteer to connect with the campaign and to stay up-to-date.

Features include:

  • make their calls and request new ones when needed
  • request post cards and track their status
  • Be shown links controlled by the campaign
  • Schedule to host a meet and greet

While writing good code is always ideal, we should really focus on producing a great experience for the volunteer. Word-of-mouth advertising is the best way to get people wanting to use Hubble. If we’re able to create a situation where volunteers only want to work on campaigns that are using Hubble then that might nudge candidates towards adoring our services. Therefore, we’ll be in a stronger position to take on market and party leaders.

With that in mind, we should take the time to ensure the experience is as simple as possible.

  • Explore removing the need to click on Call Sessions in the side bar for a volunteer to see their assigned work.
  • Resolve any issues related to emails being sent when joining Hubble.
  • Make sure all screens work on mobile and tablet devices.
  • Ensure invite and registration process are well explained
  • Easy to reach out for assistance

item.title: [HUB-151] Ward Captains
item.description:
Goals

As a Ward Captain, I need to be able to accomplish the following tasks when I’m making calls to voters within my ward.

  • Capture their email address and schedule emails to be sent to the new address
  • Adding any number of tags to a contact that indicates their desire to have a yard sign or willingness to contribute in the form of stamps.
  • Adding any number of volunteer duties to a contact

As a Campaign Manager or Volunteer Coordinator, I need to be able to:

  • run a report for all contacts on my campaign that have a specific tag.
  • add and remove tags from contacts

As a Campaign Manager, I also need to be able to create emails that can be sent to my Contacts.

As a Contact receiving emails, I need the ability to unsubscribe from emails that are sent to me by a committee using Hubble.

As Hubble, I need to be able to send emails to contacts using an address like campaign@joelnewby.com

comments.comment: Joel Newby Here is an issue to track the progress of the work from our conversations today. Let me know your thoughts!
